Of course, this is a cubic.  We already have three roots, so everything we know about root, can be expressed in terms of $a$.
Let's write a polynomial with these roots: $(x-a)(x-b)(x-c)=x^3-x^2(a+b+c)+x(ab+bc+ca)-abc$.
Plug in the values given:
\begin{align*}
x^3-x^2(2)+x(-7)-(-14) &= 0\\
x^3-2x^2-7x+14 &= 0
\end{align*}
